HEADWORD: Tattersalls
<hw>Tat"ter*sall's</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A famous horse
market in London, established in 1766 by Richard Tattersall, also used
as the headquarters of credit betting on English horse races; hence, a
large horse market elsewhere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

